# Deployment Rules

## Git Workflow

### Branch Naming
```bash
feature/user-authentication
fix/console-log-removal
refactor/database-queries
docs/update-readme
```

### Commit Messages
```bash
feat: add user authentication
fix: remove console.log statements
refactor: use TABLE_NAMES constants
docs: update API documentation
```

## Pre-Commit Checklist

```bash
# 1. TypeScript check (REQUIRED)
npm run typecheck

# 2. Lint check
npm run lint

# 3. Find console.log
grep -r "console\." src/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"

# 4. Test locally
npm run dev
```

## Deployment Process

```bash
# 1. Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/my-feature

# 2. Make changes and test
npm run dev
npm run typecheck
npm run lint

# 3. Commit
git add .
git commit -m "feat: description"

# 4. Push and create PR
git push origin feature/my-feature
```

## Protected Files - NEVER Delete

- `cms-api/src/migrations/*`
- `scripts/db/migrations/*`
- `.env*` files
- `docs/*`

## Environment Variables

```bash
# Required
DATABASE_URL=
POSTGRES_HOST=
POSTGRES_PORT=5433
POSTGRES_DB=revampit_cms
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=

# Auth
JWT_SECRET=
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
NEXTAUTH_URL=
```

## Emergency Rollback

```bash
# Revert last commit
git revert HEAD
git push origin main

# Or reset to previous commit
git reset --hard <commit-hash>
git push origin main --force  # Use with caution
```

## Don't

- Commit directly to `main`
- Force push to `main` (except emergency)
- Delete migration files
- Commit `.env` files
- Skip `npm run typecheck`
- Deploy without local testing
